	"keywords": "Jamstack, javascript, Gatsby, Netlify, Reactjs",
	"description": "When interacting with a backend, a JAMstack app can do everything a mobile app\ncan do, without the tyranny of the app store. This is a fundamental insight that\ngoes as deep as the fight for a more open, secure, decoupled, faster web.\n\nStatic site generators (SSGs) are traditionally used to generate markup HTML for\nstatic sites, and even e-commerce sites\n[https://css-tricks.com/lets-build-a-jamstack-e-commerce-store-with-netlify-functions/]\n, but the modern generation of JavaScript SSGs are enabl",
